"Had on tap. Has a smoky, peaty nose bordering on dirty wool socks. It pours brilliant copper amber with a thin film of a head. Presents a very clean and smooth palate with a little smoke, dark kettle sugars and lightly toasted malts. The palate is close to an American interpretation of a Scottish ale while it has the clean and smooth character of a lager. Medium body and carbonation."
